The paper deals with low-rank matrix approximation, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of weighted nuclear norm minimization is a technique that is relevant to all of these sub-categories.
